PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F388A1781855274
OL,3,CArchaeologists uncover 5,000-year-old
OL,4,CStonehenge 'prototype'
OL,6,FArchaeologists have made a "once in a
OL,7,Flifetime" discovery of a 5,000-year-
OL,8,Fold structure thought to have been
OL,9,Fused as a Stonehenge "prototype".
OL,11,FA team of experts uncovered it at an
OL,12,Farea three miles from the world-famous
OL,13,Fstone circle, in Wiltshire.
OL,15,FThe structure predates the main
OL,16,Fmonument at Stonehenge by around 500
OL,17,Fyears, and is the earliest known
OL,18,Falignment with the solstice in the
OL,19,Fwider archaeology-rich landscape.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
