OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,389,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F388A1781855274
OL,3,CArchaeologists uncover 5,000-year-old
OL,4,CStonehenge 'prototype'
OL,6,FIt comes as thousands of people are
OL,7,Fexpected to visit the World Heritage
OL,8,FSite this Sunday to mark the summer
OL,9,Fsolstice.
OL,11,FA Wessex Archaeology team led by TV's
OL,12,FTime Team archaeologist Dr Phil
OL,13,FHarding originally began excavating
OL,14,Fthe site at Bulford between 2015 and
OL,15,F2017.
OL,17,FThe work was commissioned to support
OL,18,Fthe Ministry of Defence's (MoD)
OL,19,Fprogramme to expand troop numbers in
OL,20,Fthe Salisbury Plain area.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,389,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F388A1781855274
OL,3,CArchaeologists uncover 5,000-year-old
OL,4,CStonehenge 'prototype'
OL,6,FTeams uncovered 48 pits - which were
OL,7,Fradiocarbon dated to around 2950 BC -
OL,8,Fwithin a 13-hectare (32 acre) area.
OL,10,FIt was in these pits that they found
OL,11,Fevidence of a structure that would
OL,12,Fhave originally consisted of two
OL,13,Fwooden poles 120 metres apart.
OL,15,FRather than debris, archaeologists
OL,16,Ffound the pits were filled with chalk,
OL,17,Fwhich would once have supported the
OL,18,Fpoles.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,389,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F388A1781855274
OL,3,CArchaeologists uncover 5,000-year-old
OL,4,CStonehenge 'prototype'
OL,6,FExperts say these would have been
OL,7,Faligned to point directly at the
OL,8,Frising sun during the summer solstice
OL,9,Fand the setting sun at the winter
OL,10,Fsolstice.
OL,12,FPottery, animal bone, worked flints
OL,13,Fand charcoal, suggesting large numbers
OL,14,Fof people gathered over a relatively
OL,15,Fshort period to celebrate the sun,
OL,16,Fwere also discovered.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,389,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F388A1781855274
OL,3,CArchaeologists uncover 5,000-year-old
OL,4,CStonehenge 'prototype'
OL,6,FOne of the pits, which it is thought
OL,7,Fmight have been a "viewing station"
OL,8,Ffor the solstice, contained a very
OL,9,Frare disc-shaped knife that was
OL,10,Fdeliberately placed there - possibly
OL,11,Fas a symbolic reference to the sun
OL,12,Fdisc, the experts said.
OL,14,FDr Harding said he had been blown away
OL,15,Fby the scale of the post pits,
OL,16,Fprompting him to consider what they
OL,17,Fwere for, before he joined them up and
OL,18,Frealised their alignment.
OL,20,F"I don't know whether you call it a
OL,21,Fgiggle moment," he said.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,389,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F388A1781855274
OL,3,CArchaeologists uncover 5,000-year-old
OL,4,CStonehenge 'prototype'
OL,6,F"Opportunities like this come along
OL,7,Fonce in a career, once in a lifetime.
OL,9,F"I'm probably towards the end of my
OL,10,Fcareer now, but thank God I'm still in
OL,11,Farchaeology long enough to be part of
OL,12,Fthis discovery, because it's certainly
OL,13,Fthe highlight of my career."
OL,15,FThe site, which is now MoD housing, is
OL,16,Fnot accessible to the public and Dr
OL,17,FHarding said one of the post pits was
OL,18,Fnow probably "under someone's front
OL,19,Froom", though the other is in an open
OL,20,Frecreational area, and still visible.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,389,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F388A1781855274
OL,3,CArchaeologists uncover 5,000-year-old
OL,4,CStonehenge 'prototype'
OL,6,FHe added: "In a few days' time,
OL,7,FStonehenge will be filled with people
OL,8,Fcelebrating midsummer solstice.
OL,10,F"But what few will realise is that
OL,11,F5,000 years ago on a nearby hillside
OL,12,Foverlooking modern day Bulford, people
OL,13,Fwere doing the exact same thing -
OL,14,Frevering and celebrating the sunrise
OL,15,Fon Midsummer's Day."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
